     "text": [
      "The sky appears blue because of a phenomenon called Rayleigh Scattering.\n",
      "When sunlight enters Earth's atmosphere, it interacts with nitrogen and oxygen molecules. These interactions cause the light to scatter in all directions.\n",
      "The scattered light makes up much of the blue light that we see when we look up at the sky.\n",
      "In summary, the sky appears blue because of Rayleigh Scattering.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
